1. To Run all functions in a file:
 >>type- [pytest] or [python -m pytest in the terminal end enter]
 Ex: pytest or
     python -m pytest

2. To Run all files:
 >>type- [pytest] or [python -m pytest in the terminal end enter]
 Ex: pytest or
     python -m pytest

3.To run specific file:
 >>type- [pytest .\package name\file name] or [python -m pytest .\package name\file name]
 EX: pytest .\6_Pytest\test_demo1.py or
     python -m pytest .\6_Pytest\test_demo1.py

4.To run specific functions from specific file:
>>type- [pytest .\package name\file name -k {function name/substring}] or [python -m pytest .\package name\file name -k {function name/substring}]
 Ex: pytest .\6_Pytest\test_demo1.py -k add or
     python -m pytest .\6_Pytest\test_demo1.py -k add

5.Grouping test:
>>pytest -m <markname> -v
Ex: python -m pytest .\6_Pytest\test_demo3.py -m valid -v

6. To see test details:
>> add -v at the last
Ex: 1. pytest -v or
       python -m pytest -v

    2. pytest .\6_Pytest\test_demo1.py -v or
       python -m pytest .\6_Pytest\test_demo1.py -v

    3. pytest .\6_Pytest\test_demo1.py -k add -v or
       python -m pytest .\6_Pytest\test_demo1.py -k add -v

6. To Generate report:
>> Install pytest-html-reporter